.TH MAIDENHEAD 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
maidenhead \- calculate a Maidenhead grid square from latitude and longitude
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B maidenhead
.I latitude longitude
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B maidenhead
validates the given coordinates and computes the six\-character Maidenhead
grid square with
.BR maidenhead.py .
.PP
This is the same calculation DigiHub uses internally whenever latitude or
longitude changes (during installation, in
.BR dhedit (1),
and in
.BR dhgpsmonitor (1)).
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I latitude
Decimal degrees, \-90 to 90. Required.
.TP
.I longitude
Decimal degrees, \-180 to 180. Required.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Calculate the grid square for a coordinate:
.B maidenhead 28.1899 \-82.50036
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/maidenhead.py
Performs the coordinate validation and grid calculation.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Grid square calculated and printed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
The supplied coordinates are out of range.
.TP
.B 2
Incorrect syntax (latitude and/or longitude were not supplied, or could
not be parsed as numbers).
.SH AUTHOR
Steve de Bode \- W0FFS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR position (1)
